The Vice President visited Detroit Metropolitan Airport in Michigan and had conversations about voting rights and COVID-19 vaccinations. She expressed concern about the efforts to suppress the vote and emphasized the importance of people understanding their rights and being engaged. Regarding vaccinations, she reminded people that vaccines are safe, free, and will save lives. She highlighted the fact that the majority of hospitalized and deceased COVID-19 patients are unvaccinated. The Vice President also discussed the significance of considering the impact on family and friends when deciding whether or not to get vaccinated. She mentioned ongoing efforts to support voting rights legislation and increase awareness about the situation in different states. The Vice President commended the Texas legislators who are standing against voter suppression and mentioned the need for a multilateral approach involving litigation, legislation, and community building. She was unsure if she would meet with the Texas legislators if they come to D.C.